  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but flashes a critical H4 divergence fading to 0, while CHF surges to H4 CSM 100 from D1 zero and NZD accelerates to H4 82 from D1 5, making these the two most important short-term signals in this brief against a Risk-Off Medium regime anchored by strong US PMI data. USDCHF is the primary expression as CHF strength directly counters fading USD momentum, while NZDUSD and AUDUSD benefit from NZD and AUD H4 acceleration with VIX declining 3.9 percent and copper up 0.82 percent adding cyclical tailwinds.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nFed speaker follow-up to Barkin guidance eschewment hits USDJPY directly, where JPY holds D1 CSM rank third at 34 and any dovish Fed repricing accelerates USD fade already visible in H4.\nUS-Iran nuclear deal progress compresses Middle East risk premium and pressures Gold below 4541, triggering XAUUSD long unwind and reducing safe-haven flow into USDCHF.\nWTI Oil decline continuation through 97.00 weakens CADJPY given CAD sits weakest on H4 CSM at 44 with energy correlation intact.",
